$ Shell command: zip
@ zip

`zip` packages and compresses archive files.

code {
zip target.zip file.txt
code }

All files in a directory:
code {
zip -r target.zip directory
code }
It includes the directory name as well as `.*` files.

{ Showing content of a zip file

code {
unzip -l target.zip
code }

}
{ Unzipping into a specific directory

code {
unzip file.zip -d /some/directory
code }

}

